OL,3,CUnpaid carer left feeling more support
OL,4,Cwill only be available when she dies
OL,6,FSylvia Penny has an unbreakable bond
OL,7,Fwith her children.
OL,9,FWidowed when they were young, she has
OL,10,Fdedicated more than 40 years of her
OL,11,Flife to their ongoing care needs.
OL,13,FShe provides round-the-clock care for
OL,14,Fher daughter Michelle, who is 95%
OL,15,Fbedbound with ME, or chronic fatigue
OL,16,Fsyndrome, and her severely autistic
OL,17,Fson David.
OL,19,FSylvia believes there are a lot of
OL,20,Fmisconceptions about the jobs which
OL,21,Funpaid carers do on a day-to-day basis.
