OL,6,FShe said: "(The public) has the
OL,7,Fperception that a carer sits down and
OL,8,Fhas a cup of tea and a piece of cake
OL,9,Fwith somebody. They think that's all
OL,10,Fyou do.
OL,12,F"They don't realise you're responsible
OL,13,Ffor somebody's medicine, their health
OL,14,Fand well-being, their finances and
OL,15,Ftheir happiness - everything.
OL,17,F"It's like looking after a newborn
OL,18,Fbaby, it's that type of responsibility
OL,19,Fbut I don't think the general public
OL,20,Fknow that or understand it.
