OL,6,FAsked how she would want her local
OL,7,Fauthority - Vale of Glamorgan - to
OL,8,Fhelp her so she can continue carrying
OL,9,Fout her caring responsibilities,
OL,10,FSylvia said: "It would be nice if I
OL,11,Fcould have a life where one day a week
OL,12,FI could meet friends, go to the
OL,13,Fmuseum, go to a gallery, to do the
OL,14,Fthings that I like to do without
OL,15,Fhaving to consider someone else's
OL,16,Fneeds first.
OL,18,F"But I don't think there's any
OL,19,Fprospect of that in the near future
OL,20,Fbecause finances are so stretched, and
OL,21,Fthere are people worse off than me."
